## ERR

### 5. useanimatedgesturehandler-removed

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { useAnimatedGestureHandler } from "react-native-reanimated";
const handler = useAnimatedGestureHandler({ onActive: (e, ctx) => { ... } });
return <PanGestureHandler onGestureEvent={handler}>...</PanGestureHandler>;
```

**Why wrong:** `useAnimatedGestureHandler` and the imperative `PanGestureHandler` JSX wrappers are removed in Reanimated 4. SDK 55 ships Reanimated 4.2.1.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { Gesture, GestureDetector } from "react-native-gesture-handler";
import { useSharedValue, useAnimatedStyle } from "react-native-reanimated";

const x = useSharedValue(0);
const pan = Gesture.Pan().onUpdate((e) => {
  x.value = e.translationX;
});
const style = useAnimatedStyle(() => ({ transform: [{ translateX: x.value }] }));
return <GestureDetector gesture={pan}><Animated.View style={style} /></GestureDetector>;
```

Source: https://docs.swmansion.com/react-native-gesture-handler/docs/gestures/gesture/

### 6. legacy-camera-import

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { Camera } from "expo-camera";
return <Camera ref={ref} type={Camera.Constants.Type.back} />;
```

**Why wrong:** The legacy `Camera` export and `Camera.Constants` were removed in SDK 52. SDK 55's `expo-camera` ships `CameraView` plus the `useCameraPermissions` hook.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { CameraView, useCameraPermissions } from "expo-camera";
const [permission, requestPermission] = useCameraPermissions();
if (!permission?.granted) return <Button onPress={requestPermission} title="Allow" />;
return <CameraView facing="back" />;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/camera/

### 7. missing-root-layout

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** `app/index.tsx` exists but no `app/_layout.tsx`.

**Why wrong:** Expo Router requires that the root layout renders a navigator (Stack, Tabs, Drawer, or Slot) on its FIRST render. A missing or conditional `_layout.tsx` produces the runtime error: "Attempted to navigate before mounting the Root Layout component".

**Canonical:**

```tsx
// app/_layout.tsx
import { Stack } from "expo-router";
export default function RootLayout() {
  return <Stack />;
}
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/advanced/root-layout/

### 8. navigationcontainer-in-expo-router

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { NavigationContainer } from "@react-navigation/native";
return <NavigationContainer>{children}</NavigationContainer>;
```

**Why wrong:** Expo Router instantiates its own `NavigationContainer` internally. Wrapping it again throws "Another navigator is already registered for this container".

**Canonical:** Remove `NavigationContainer`. Use `<Stack />` / `<Tabs />` / `<Slot />` from `expo-router` inside `_layout.tsx`.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/migrate/from-react-navigation/

### 9. createstacknavigator-in-expo-router

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
const Stack = createStackNavigator();
<Stack.Navigator>
  <Stack.Screen name="Home" component={HomeScreen} />
</Stack.Navigator>
```

**Why wrong:** Expo Router is file-based. `createStackNavigator` / `createBottomTabNavigator` are not compatible with the router's filesystem convention; routes are inferred from files in `app/`.

**Canonical:** Move `HomeScreen` to `app/index.tsx`. Configure stack options via `<Stack.Screen options={{...}} />` inside `_layout.tsx` or per-file `<Stack.Screen options={...} />` from `expo-router`.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/basics/layout/#stack

### 10. worklets-plugin-missing

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```js
// babel.config.js
module.exports = function (api) {
  api.cache(true);
  return {
    presets: ["babel-preset-expo"],
    plugins: ["react-native-reanimated/plugin"],
  };
};
```

**Why wrong:** Reanimated 4 (shipped with SDK 55) moved its Babel plugin into the new `react-native-worklets` package. The old `react-native-reanimated/plugin` path no longer exists and produces "Reanimated 2 failed to create a worklet" at runtime.

**Canonical:**

```js
module.exports = function (api) {
  api.cache(true);
  return {
    presets: ["babel-preset-expo"],
    plugins: ["react-native-worklets/plugin"],
  };
};
```

The worklets plugin must be the LAST plugin in the list.

Source: https://docs.swmansion.com/react-native-reanimated/docs/guides/migration-from-3.x/

### 11. package-exports-cjs-esm-dual

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Adding a library that ships broken `package.json` "exports" (dual CJS/ESM) without verifying it loads under Metro.

**Why wrong:** RN 0.79 enabled Metro's `package.json` "exports" resolver by default. Many older libs declare exports but their `.cjs` and `.mjs` entries diverge, producing "interop default" runtime crashes.

**Canonical:** Bump the library to a version that publishes correct exports, or pin a known-good version. If urgent, opt out in `metro.config.js`:

```js
const { getDefaultConfig } = require("expo/metro-config");
const config = getDefaultConfig(__dirname);
config.resolver.unstable_enablePackageExports = false; // last resort
module.exports = config;
```

Source: https://github.com/facebook/metro/issues/670

### 12. classic-expo-cli

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```json
// package.json
{
  "dependencies": { "expo-cli": "^6.0.0" },
  "scripts": {
    "start": "expo start",
    "build": "expo build:android"
  }
}
```

**Why wrong:** The classic `expo-cli` (global) was deprecated in 2022 and removed for new projects. SDK 55 uses the local CLI `npx expo` and EAS Build/Submit/Update for native builds.

**Canonical:**

```json
{
  "scripts": {
    "start": "npx expo start",
    "android": "npx expo run:android",
    "ios": "npx expo run:ios",
    "build:android": "eas build -p android --profile production"
  }
}
```

Source: https://blog.expo.dev/the-new-expo-cli-f4250d8e3421

### 13. missing-expo-notifications-plugin

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Using `expo-notifications` API without adding the config plugin to `app.config.ts`.

**Why wrong:** CNG generates native code from the `plugins` array. If `expo-notifications` is not listed, the APNs entitlement is missing on iOS and `expo prebuild --clean` wipes any manual edits.

**Canonical:**

```ts
// app.config.ts
plugins: [
  "expo-router",
  [
    "expo-notifications",
    {
      icon: "./assets/notification-icon.png",
      color: "#ffffff",
      defaultChannel: "default",
    },
  ],
],
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/notifications/#configuration

### 14. push-in-expo-go-android

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Testing remote push on Android in Expo Go.

**Why wrong:** Remote push notifications on Android were removed from Expo Go in SDK 53. They require a development build via `eas build --profile development`.

**Canonical:** Use `npx expo install expo-dev-client`, run `eas build -p android --profile development`, install the build on the device, then test remote push.

Source: https://expo.dev/changelog/sdk-53

### 15. splashscreen-no-hide

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import * as SplashScreen from "expo-splash-screen";
SplashScreen.preventAutoHideAsync();
// ... but never call SplashScreen.hideAsync()
```

**Why wrong:** `preventAutoHideAsync` blocks the splash from hiding. Without a matching `hideAsync`, the splash stays forever and the app appears frozen at launch.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
SplashScreen.preventAutoHideAsync();
const [loaded] = useFonts({ Inter: require("./assets/fonts/Inter.ttf") });
const onLayout = useCallback(async () => {
  if (loaded) await SplashScreen.hideAsync();
}, [loaded]);
if (!loaded) return null;
return <View onLayout={onLayout}>...</View>;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/splash-screen/

### 16. missing-scheme-for-oauth

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Setting up `expo-auth-session` without a `scheme` in `app.config.ts`.

**Why wrong:** Without `scheme`, the OAuth provider redirect cannot deep-link back into the app. The browser opens but the callback never reaches the JS bundle.

**Canonical:**

```ts
// app.config.ts
export default {
  expo: {
    scheme: "myapp",
    // ...
  },
};
```

And use `AuthSession.makeRedirectUri({ scheme: "myapp" })`.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/auth-session/#redirect-uri

### 17. runtime-version-mismatch-on-native-change

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```ts
// app.config.ts
runtimeVersion: "1.0.0",
```

then bump a native dependency without touching `runtimeVersion`.

**Why wrong:** Static `runtimeVersion` strings get out of sync the moment native code changes. EAS Update pushes JS to clients whose native shell does not match. App crashes on launch.

**Canonical:**

```ts
runtimeVersion: { policy: "fingerprint" },
```

`policy: "fingerprint"` hashes every input that affects native code; updates are gated to matching builds automatically.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/eas-update/runtime-versions/#fingerprint-runtime-version-policy

### 18. edge-to-edge-statusbar-overlap

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Targeting SDK 55 without using `SafeAreaView` / `useSafeAreaInsets` at the top of screens.

**Why wrong:** SDK 53 enabled edge-to-edge by default on Android. SDK 55 keeps it enabled. Content draws under the status bar; top buttons become untouchable.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { SafeAreaView } from "react-native-safe-area-context";
return <SafeAreaView edges={["top"]}>...</SafeAreaView>;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/develop/user-interface/safe-areas/

### 19. manual-android-ios-edits

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:** Hand-editing `ios/MyApp/Info.plist` or `android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`.

**Why wrong:** CNG (Continuous Native Generation) wipes `ios/` and `android/` on `npx expo prebuild --clean`. Manual edits silently disappear on the next build.

**Canonical:** Express native config via a config plugin in `app.config.ts`:

```ts
plugins: [
  [
    "expo-build-properties",
    {
      ios: { deploymentTarget: "15.1" },
      android: { compileSdkVersion: 35, targetSdkVersion: 35 },
    },
  ],
],
```

For one-off entitlements, write a tiny config plugin under `plugins/`.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/workflow/continuous-native-generation/

### 20. expo-permissions-import

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```ts
import * as Permissions from "expo-permissions";
await Permissions.askAsync(Permissions.CAMERA);
```

**Why wrong:** `expo-permissions` was deprecated in SDK 41 and removed entirely. Each module ships its own permission API.

**Canonical:**

```ts
import { useCameraPermissions } from "expo-camera";
import * as Location from "expo-location";
await Location.requestForegroundPermissionsAsync();
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/permissions/ (redirect note)

### 21. navigate-replaces-stacknav

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
router.navigate("/feed");
```

after pushing several screens, expecting it to pop back to `/feed`.

**Why wrong:** `router.navigate` is not a pop-to-existing helper. It follows React Navigation 7 navigate semantics, which may add a new screen rather than collapse the stack back to an existing one. If your intent is to surface a route that is already on the stack (and unwind the screens above it), reach for `router.dismissTo`. Reserve `router.navigate` for "go to this URL, I do not care whether the stack grows".

**Canonical:**

```tsx
router.dismissTo("/feed");
// or pop one
router.back();
// or replace
router.replace("/feed");
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/reference/redirects/

### 22. reanimated-3-with-sdk-55

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```json
{ "dependencies": { "react-native-reanimated": "^3.10.0" } }
```

**Why wrong:** SDK 54 bumped Reanimated to 4.x. SDK 55 ships Reanimated 4.2.1. v3 will not build against RN 0.83 + the worklets plugin split.

**Canonical:**

```json
{ "dependencies": { "react-native-reanimated": "~4.2.1", "react-native-worklets": "0.7.4" } }
```

Always run `npx expo install` so versions match the SDK 55 compatibility matrix.

Source: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/sdk-55/packages/expo/bundledNativeModules.json

### 23. flashlist-v1-with-sdk-55

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { FlashList } from "@shopify/flash-list";
<FlashList data={items} estimatedItemSize={64} renderItem={...} />
```

with `"@shopify/flash-list": "^1.6.0"`.

**Why wrong:** SDK 54+ ships FlashList 2.x which auto-measures. `estimatedItemSize` is a no-op (warning only) in v2, and v1 will not build against RN 0.83's New Architecture.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { FlashList } from "@shopify/flash-list"; // v2
<FlashList data={items} renderItem={({ item }) => <Row item={item} />} keyExtractor={(it) => it.id} />
```

Pin: `"@shopify/flash-list": "2.0.2"`.

Source: https://shopify.github.io/flash-list/docs/v2-changes

### 24. expo-file-system-classic-default-assumed

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```ts
import * as FileSystem from "expo-file-system";
await FileSystem.writeAsStringAsync(FileSystem.documentDirectory + "x.txt", "hi");
```

**Why wrong:** In SDK 54+, the default `expo-file-system` export is the NEW `File`/`Directory` API. The classic functional API moved to `expo-file-system/legacy`. The above call still exists only as a deprecated re-export.

**Canonical (new API):**

```ts
import { File, Directory, Paths } from "expo-file-system";
const file = new File(Paths.document, "x.txt");
await file.write("hi");
const text = await file.text();
```

If you must keep the old code working short-term:

```ts
import * as FileSystem from "expo-file-system/legacy";
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/filesystem/

### 25. expo-av-imports

**Severity:** ERR

**Tempting:**

```ts
import { Video, Audio } from "expo-av";
```

**Why wrong:** `expo-av` was removed from Expo Go in SDK 55. The split modules `expo-video` and `expo-audio` are the supported APIs and are simpler to use.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { useVideoPlayer, VideoView } from "expo-video";
import { useAudioPlayer } from "expo-audio";

const player = useVideoPlayer(uri, (p) => { p.play(); });
return <VideoView player={player} style={{ flex: 1 }} contentFit="contain" />;
```

Source: https://expo.dev/changelog/sdk-55

