## WARN

### 26. rn-image-for-remote-content

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { Image } from "react-native";
<Image source={{ uri }} style={{ width: 200, height: 200 }} />
```

**Why wrong:** `react-native` `Image` has no built-in caching, no placeholder, no transition, no priority queue. For remote content `expo-image` is faster and uses less memory.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { Image } from "expo-image";
<Image
  source={uri}
  contentFit="cover"
  cachePolicy="memory-disk"
  transition={200}
  placeholder={require("./assets/blurhash.png")}
  style={{ width: 200, height: 200 }}
/>;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/image/

### 27. resizemode-on-expo-image

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
<Image source={...} resizeMode="cover" />
```

with `expo-image`.

**Why wrong:** `resizeMode` is the `react-native` Image prop. `expo-image` uses `contentFit`. `resizeMode` is silently ignored.

**Canonical:** `contentFit="cover" | "contain" | "fill" | "none" | "scale-down"`.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/image/#contentfit

### 28. react-native-fast-image-import

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```ts
import FastImage from "react-native-fast-image";
```

**Why wrong:** `react-native-fast-image` is unmaintained (archived 2023) and not New-Architecture compatible. `expo-image` is the supported replacement and is faster on RN 0.83.

**Canonical:** Replace with `expo-image` (see #26).

Source: https://github.com/DylanVann/react-native-fast-image (archived)

### 29. asyncstorage-for-kv

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```ts
import AsyncStorage from "@react-native-async-storage/async-storage";
await AsyncStorage.setItem("preferred_theme", "dark");
```

**Why wrong:** `AsyncStorage` is JSON-on-disk, single-file, no transactions. `expo-sqlite/kv-store` is the New-Architecture-native drop-in: same API, backed by SQLite WAL.

**Canonical:**

```ts
import AsyncStorage from "expo-sqlite/kv-store";
await AsyncStorage.setItem("preferred_theme", "dark");
```

Same surface, faster reads, atomic writes.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/async-storage/

### 30. animated-api-for-new-code

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { Animated } from "react-native";
const value = useRef(new Animated.Value(0)).current;
Animated.timing(value, { toValue: 1, useNativeDriver: true }).start();
```

**Why wrong:** The legacy `Animated` API runs on the JS thread for most operations (only certain transforms use the native driver). Reanimated 4 worklets run on the UI thread.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { useSharedValue, useAnimatedStyle, withTiming } from "react-native-reanimated";
const opacity = useSharedValue(0);
useEffect(() => { opacity.value = withTiming(1); }, []);
const style = useAnimatedStyle(() => ({ opacity: opacity.value }));
```

Source: https://docs.swmansion.com/react-native-reanimated/

### 31. flatlist-for-large-lists

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
<FlatList data={thousandItems} renderItem={...} />
```

**Why wrong:** `FlatList` is fine for short lists. For 200+ items, FlashList 2's recycling is significantly faster and more memory-efficient.

**Canonical:** Use `FlashList` from `@shopify/flash-list` 2.x.

Source: https://shopify.github.io/flash-list/

### 32. flashlist-v1-estimateditemsize-carryover

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
<FlashList data={items} estimatedItemSize={64} renderItem={...} />
```

with FlashList 2.x.

**Why wrong:** FlashList 2 auto-measures item size on the JS thread. `estimatedItemSize` is a deprecated no-op in v2 and emits a warning on first render.

**Canonical:** Remove `estimatedItemSize`. If you need stable indexes for sticky headers, add `getItemType`.

Source: https://shopify.github.io/flash-list/docs/v2-changes

### 33. useeffect-auth-redirect

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  if (!session) router.replace("/sign-in");
}, [session]);
```

**Why wrong:** This pattern flashes the protected route for one frame, runs after layout, and double-redirects on hot reload. Expo Router 55 ships `Stack.Protected` which is declarative and pre-render gated.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
// app/_layout.tsx
<Stack>
  <Stack.Protected guard={!!session}>
    <Stack.Screen name="(app)" />
  </Stack.Protected>
  <Stack.Protected guard={!session}>
    <Stack.Screen name="(auth)" />
  </Stack.Protected>
</Stack>
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/advanced/authentication/

### 34. useroute-useparams-in-expo-router

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
import { useRoute } from "@react-navigation/native";
const route = useRoute();
const id = route.params.id;
```

**Why wrong:** Expo Router supplies `useLocalSearchParams`. `useRoute` works but bypasses the typed routes generator.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { useLocalSearchParams } from "expo-router";
const { id } = useLocalSearchParams<{ id: string }>();
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/reference/hooks/

### 35. untyped-search-params

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
const params = useLocalSearchParams();
const id: string = params.id; // unsafe
```

**Why wrong:** Without the type parameter, `params.id` is `string | string[] | undefined`. Production crashes from `id.toLowerCase()` calls trace back here.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
const { id } = useLocalSearchParams<{ id: string }>();
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/router/reference/typed-routes/

### 36. react-native-fs-import

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```ts
import RNFS from "react-native-fs";
await RNFS.writeFile(RNFS.DocumentDirectoryPath + "/x.txt", "hi", "utf8");
```

**Why wrong:** `react-native-fs` is bare-RN-only and not maintained for the New Architecture. Expo ships first-party `expo-file-system` with the same surface.

**Canonical:**

```ts
import { File, Paths } from "expo-file-system";
const file = new File(Paths.document, "x.txt");
await file.write("hi");
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/filesystem/

### 37. react-native-vector-icons-import

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```ts
import Icon from "react-native-vector-icons/MaterialIcons";
```

**Why wrong:** `react-native-vector-icons` requires manual native linking and `app.json` font registration. `@expo/vector-icons` ships the same icon sets pre-linked through CNG.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { MaterialIcons } from "@expo/vector-icons";
<MaterialIcons name="home" size={24} color="black" />;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/icons/

### 38. enablehermes-jsengine-noop

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```json
// app.json
{ "expo": { "jsEngine": "hermes" } }
```

**Why wrong:** Hermes has been the default since SDK 49 / SDK 53. Setting `jsEngine: "hermes"` is a no-op; setting `jsEngine: "jsc"` opts INTO a deprecated engine. The flag should be omitted entirely.

**Canonical:** Omit the field.

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/using-hermes/

### 39. bridgeless-explicit

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```json
{ "expo": { "newArchEnabled": true, "experiments": { "bridgeless": true } } }
```

**Why wrong:** SDK 55 dropped Legacy Architecture entirely. The New Architecture (bridgeless) is the only mode. Setting `newArchEnabled: true` is noise; setting it to `false` will be ignored.

**Canonical:** Omit both fields.

Source: https://expo.dev/changelog/sdk-55

### 40. missing-expo-dev-client

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:** Using a native module that is not part of Expo Go (e.g. a custom config plugin or third-party native package) and continuing to develop in Expo Go.

**Why wrong:** Expo Go ships a fixed set of native modules. Anything outside that set throws "Unimplemented module" at runtime. The fix is a development build.

**Canonical:**

```sh
npx expo install expo-dev-client
eas build -p ios --profile development
eas build -p android --profile development
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/develop/development-builds/introduction/

### 41. useanimatedreaction-vs-render-read

**Severity:** WARN

**Tempting:**

```tsx
const value = useSharedValue(0);
return <Text>{value.value}</Text>;
```

**Why wrong:** Reading `.value` outside a worklet / animated style is undefined behavior. The render thread sees a stale snapshot and never re-runs when the shared value changes.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import Animated, { useAnimatedProps } from "react-native-reanimated";
const AnimatedText = Animated.createAnimatedComponent(TextInput);
const props = useAnimatedProps(() => ({ text: String(value.value) }));
return <AnimatedText editable={false} animatedProps={props} />;
```

Or pipe to React state via `useAnimatedReaction` + `runOnJS`.

Source: https://docs.swmansion.com/react-native-reanimated/docs/core/useSharedValue

