## NIT

### 42. app-json-not-app-config-ts

**Severity:** NIT

**Tempting:** Keeping `app.json` only.

**Why wrong:** Static JSON cannot read `process.env` or branch on `EAS_BUILD_PROFILE`. Almost every real project needs at least one env-driven value (API base, OAuth client id).

**Canonical:** Migrate to `app.config.ts`:

```ts
import { ExpoConfig } from "expo/config";
const config: ExpoConfig = {
  name: "MyApp",
  slug: "myapp",
  scheme: "myapp",
  runtimeVersion: { policy: "fingerprint" },
  extra: { apiBase: process.env.API_BASE },
  plugins: ["expo-router", "expo-secure-store"],
};
export default config;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/workflow/configuration/

### 43. usefonts-without-render-gate

**Severity:** NIT

**Tempting:**

```tsx
useFonts({ Inter: require("./assets/fonts/Inter.ttf") });
return <Text style={{ fontFamily: "Inter" }}>hi</Text>;
```

**Why wrong:** First paint uses the system font (FOUT) and shifts when Inter loads (CLS). Gate the render on `loaded`.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
const [loaded] = useFonts({ Inter: require("./assets/fonts/Inter.ttf") });
if (!loaded) return null;
return <Text style={{ fontFamily: "Inter" }}>hi</Text>;
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/versions/v55.0.0/sdk/font/

### 44. tsconfig-not-extending-expo

**Severity:** NIT

**Tempting:**

```json
{ "compilerOptions": { "strict": true, "jsx": "react-jsx" } }
```

**Why wrong:** Without `expo/tsconfig.base` you lose Metro-aligned `moduleResolution`, JSX runtime alignment, and the generated typed-routes types under `.expo/types/router.d.ts`.

**Canonical:**

```json
{
  "extends": "expo/tsconfig.base",
  "compilerOptions": { "strict": true },
  "include": [".expo/types/**/*.ts", "**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx"]
}
```

Source: https://docs.expo.dev/guides/typescript/

### 45. setstate-from-worklet

**Severity:** NIT

**Tempting:**

```tsx
const pan = Gesture.Pan().onUpdate((e) => {
  setX(e.translationX); // setState from worklet
});
```

**Why wrong:** Worklets run on the UI thread. React state setters live on the JS thread. Calling them directly produces silent state-update drops.

**Canonical:**

```tsx
import { runOnJS } from "react-native-reanimated";
const pan = Gesture.Pan().onUpdate((e) => {
  runOnJS(setX)(e.translationX);
});
```

Source: https://docs.swmansion.com/react-native-reanimated/docs/threading/runOnJS

